		<item>
		<title>Scott’s Solo Bass Sessions – &#8216;My Favorite Things&#8217;</title>
		<link>http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/chords/my-favourite-things-solo-bass.html</link>
		<comments>http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/chords/my-favourite-things-solo-bass.html#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Fri, 14 Nov 2014 10:39:11 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[scott]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Chords]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Live Sessions]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/?p=7587</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<p>What can I say… the response I’ve had from the last two solo bass singles that I released has completely blown me away! Collectively the two singles have had over 20,000 views in just the last month!… My mind is...</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/chords/my-favourite-things-solo-bass.html">Scott’s Solo Bass Sessions – &#8216;My Favorite Things&#8217;</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com">Online Bass Lessons</a>.</p>
]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>What can I say… the response I’ve had from the last two solo bass singles that I released has completely blown me away!</p>
<p>Collectively the two singles have had over 20,000 views in just the last month!…</p>
<p>My mind is blown! :)</p>
<p>Because of the overwhelming feedback i’ve received from you guys, I decided it was about to time to get back in the shed (my favourite place!) and get to work on another solo bass single for you.</p>
<p>This new solo single is based on the song “My Favourite Things” from the Rogers and Hammerstein musical The Sound of Music - although my version is quite different from the original as you’ll find out.</p>
<p>I used my Overwater 5 string signature bass strung E-C, and went direct into the desk.</p>
<p>Hope you enjoy this one… let me know what you think in the comments below the video.</p>
<p>As always, see you in the shed…</p>
<p>Scott.</p>
<p>PS. If you haven't check out the last two solo bass singles I release, you can check them out here...</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/live-sessions/scotts-solo-bass-sessions-smile-charlie-chaplin.html">Smile.</a></li>
